# One Piece Card List — Phase 2 Feature Upgrades

All features are **frontend-only** (no server). Data persists via `localStorage`. Features that require a backend (Price Tracker, Login, Tier Lists, Ruling FAQs, Popularity stats) are out of scope.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Price Tracker** (TCGPlayer/Cardmarket) requires a backend proxy — CORS blocks direct browser calls. Skipping for now.
> **Login / My Collection sync** requires auth — implemented with local-only localStorage instead.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Data Layer

#### [MODIFY] [cards.json](file:///d:/AntigravityProj/One-Piece-Card-List/data/cards.json)
- Add [set](file:///d:/AntigravityProj/One-Piece-Card-List/scripts/script.js#303-324) field: `"OP-09"`, `"OP-08"`, `"OP-01"`, `"OP-10"` parsed from existing IDs
- Add `crew` array: `["Red-Haired Pirates", "The Four Emperors"]`

---

### Architecture — New Tab Nav System

#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///d:/AntigravityProj/One-Piece-Card-List/html/index.html)
- Add **top nav tabs**: `Card List` | `My Deck` | `My Collection`
- Tabs show/hide the relevant `<section>` — no page reload needed
- Add **"Add to Deck"** button on each card (appears on hover strip)
- Add **"Owned"** toggle button on each card (appears on hover strip)
- **Deck panel** (`#deck-panel`): card list with quantities, count badge, export button, clear button
- **Collection panel** (`#collection-panel`): owned cards grid with quantity spinners
- Advanced filter additions to sidebar: Cost range, Power range, Set pills, Crew select
- Grid/List view toggle button in result bar
- Dark/Light mode toggle button in header

---

### CSS Additions

#### [MODIFY] [style.css](file:///d:/AntigravityProj/One-Piece-Card-List/css/style.css)
- `[data-theme="light"]` overrides for all CSS tokens → full light mode
- Tab navigation bar styles
- Deck panel: fixed right drawer or collapsible side panel
- Card action buttons (+ Add to Deck, ♥ Own) on `.card-info-strip`
- **In-deck badge**: gold pill overlay on card corner
- **Owned badge**: green check overlay on card corner
- Deck entry row styles (image thumbnail + name + count controls + remove)
- Collection view: same grid but with quantity overlay
- **Range sliders** styled for dark theme
- List view card style (horizontal compact rows)

---

### JavaScript — Additions

#### [MODIFY] [script.js](file:///d:/AntigravityProj/One-Piece-Card-List/scripts/script.js)

**Deck Builder**
- `deck` object: `{ leaderId: null, cards: { [id]: count } }`
- `addToDeck(card)` — enforces: max 4 copies, 1 Leader only, Leader must be `cardType === 'Leader'`
- `removeFromDeck(id)` — decrements or removes
- `renderDeck()` — renders deck panel rows
- `exportDeck()` — copies text list to clipboard
- `saveDeck()` / `loadDeck()` — localStorage `op-deck`
- Live deck count badge in tab label

**My Collection**
- `collection` object: `{ [id]: count }`
- `setOwned(id, qty)` / `toggleOwned(id)`
- `renderCollection()` — filtered grid of owned cards
- `saveCollection()` / `loadCollection()` — localStorage `op-collection`
- Card grid items get `.has-owned` badge when qty > 0
- Card grid items get `.in-deck` badge when in deck > 0

**Advanced Filters**
- Cost min/max slider → `state.costMin` / `state.costMax`
- Power min/max slider → `state.powerMin` / `state.powerMax`
- Set filter pills → `state.set`
- Crew filter select → `state.crew`
- All hook into [applyFilters()](file:///d:/AntigravityProj/One-Piece-Card-List/scripts/script.js#67-106)

**Related Cards in Modal**
- When modal opens, compute cards sharing same `Type` or `crew`
- Render compact thumbnails in modal footer row
- Clicking a related card navigates to it

**View Toggle**
- Toggle between `.card-grid--grid` and `.card-grid--list` class on the grid
- List view renders horizontal compact rows with all stats visible

**Dark/Light Mode**
- Button in header toggles `data-theme="light"` on `<html>`
- Persisted in localStorage

---

## Verification Plan

### Manual Testing
1. Add a Leader card → verify max 1 Leader rule enforced
2. Add 5 copies of a Character → verify capped at 4
3. Add 50 cards → verify deck full message
4. Export deck → verify clipboard text format
5. Reload page → verify deck persists from localStorage
6. Mark cards Owned → verify badge appears on card
7. Switch to Collection tab → verify only owned cards show
8. Use Cost range slider → verify cards filter correctly
9. Use Set filter → verify OP-09 only shows OP-09 cards
10. Toggle light mode → verify all panels invert cleanly
11. Toggle list view → verify compact horizontal layout
